review_blob: Very mild aroma. Light golden appearance, head does not hold. Weak taste, no carbonation, flat. Somewhat sticky on the palate. Overall not to my taste.

A Pale Ale with Bavarian charm. Wonderful aroma. Rich dark golden appearance, clean white head. Very smooth transition from a fine fruity note of Mandarina Bavaria hops towards a full bodied malty taste. Satisfying on the palate. Soft through open fermentation tanks. One of my favourite Pale Ales overall.
